One may call a Natick when two trivia entries cross - especially obscure trivia, with a crossing that can be one of many letters. The name refers to the town of Natick, which was once included in some puzzle and caused much grief because few people knew it, apparently understandably, as there was nothing special about the town - it was just one among thousands like it (at least that's what I gathered from previous discussions on this board).

Btw, I recently played Fallout 4, the post-apocalyptic video game, set in Massachusetts (or what was left of it in the game's universe). You can imagine my reaction when one of the ruined towns I discovered turned out to be... Natick!

